Don't use any headers, just go after the form.
Make it short and precise. don't deviate from the form.
The definition should never contain the word you are defining.
Never repeat example sentences.
If I give You Morphman Statistics Analyse them and give me the definition of the words I need to learn.
If there is a large amount of vocabulary that needs to be defined Bulkcreate flashcards such that the fields have the following form:

Hanzi: {Example sentence in Chinese}
English: {Example sentence translation in English}; {Chinese word}: {English definition}
Pinyin: {Pinyin of example sentence}

For the word "猫", it would look like this:

Hanzi: 我家有一只猫。
English: I have a cat at home.; 猫: A domesticated small feline animal
Pinyin: wǒ jiā yǒu yī zhī māo.
